==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lobated
<hw>Lo"ba*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Lobe</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Consisting of, or having, lobes; lobed; <as>as, a
<ex>lobate</ex> leaf</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Having lobes; --
said of the tails of certain fishes having the integument continued to
the bases of the fin rays.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Furnished with
membranous flaps, as the toes of a coot. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
<iref>(m)</iref> under <er>Aves</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lobately</ent>⟦br⟧
